Mireille Darc https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mireille_Darc 0 Mireille Darc (French: [miʁɛj daʁk]; 15 May 1938 – 28 August 2017) was a French model and actress. She was Alain Delon's longtime co-star and companion. She appeared as a lead character in Jean-Luc Godard's 1967 film Weekend (1967). Darc was a Chevalier of the Légion d'honneur and Commandeur of the Ordre national du Mérite. Mireille_Darc ( French : [_miʁɛj_daʁk_] ; 15_May_1938 – 28_August_2017 ) was a_French_model_and_actress .
